# StackBadger — test account credentials
# Copy to .env and fill in. These four values are the ONLY ones required.
# All provider config (Supabase URL + anon key, Clerk FAPI host, Firebase API
# key, etc.) is auto-discovered from the target site's JS bundle at runtime.

PENTEST_USER_A_EMAIL=
PENTEST_USER_A_PASSWORD=
PENTEST_USER_B_EMAIL=
PENTEST_USER_B_PASSWORD=

# --- Target confirmation + authorization gates (required for any REMOTE target) ---
# run.sh refuses to scan any non-localhost host (read-only mode included)
# unless BOTH values below EXACT-match the target's host. Set the bare host:
# lowercase, no scheme, no port, and NO subdomain cross-match
# (api.example.com != example.com). For a site that redirects (e.g. apex ->
# www), use the post-redirect canonical host. --yes does NOT bypass either
# gate; localhost / 127.0.0.1 are exempt.
#
# CONFIRM_TARGET — "this is the right host" (typo / wrong-environment guard).
#   Example: for ./run.sh https://staging.example.com set:
# CONFIRM_TARGET=staging.example.com
#
# CONFIRM_AUTHORIZED — "a human affirmed authorization to test this host".
#   Must be set by the site OWNER out-of-band (not by an agent following
#   LAUNCH.md). Only set this for systems you own or are explicitly
#   authorized, in writing, to test.
# CONFIRM_AUTHORIZED=staging.example.com

# --- Optional ---
# Supabase Management API token — required ONLY for --branch mode.
# SUPABASE_ACCESS_TOKEN=
# Internal-endpoint authorization secret — for internal-endpoint probes.
# PENTEST_INTERNAL_SECRET=
# Provider config overrides (normally auto-discovered; set only to override):
# SUPABASE_PROJECT_URL=
# SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=
# CLERK_FAPI_HOST=
# FIREBASE_API_KEY=
